# Copy to .env and fill in values
# These are all VITE_ (browser-exposed) — set them in Vercel / Azure SWA dashboard for prod

VITE_SUPABASE_URL=https://<project-id>.supabase.co
VITE_SUPABASE_PROJECT_ID=<project-id>
VITE_SUPABASE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=<anon-key>

VITE_ENCEPH_READ_API_BASE=https://<readapi>.azurecontainerapps.io
VITE_ENCEPH_READ_API_KEY=<api-key>

VITE_IPLANE_BASE=https://<iplane>.azurecontainerapps.io
VITE_CPLANE_BASE=https://<cplane>.azurecontainerapps.io

# Supabase Edge Function secrets (Dashboard → Edge Functions → Secrets):
# RAZORPAY_PILOT_PLAN_ID — Razorpay plan id (plan_…) for recurring pilot subscriptions
#   (create_pilot_subscription + verify_pilot_subscription). Create the plan in Razorpay first.
# CPLANE_URL — same origin as VITE_CPLANE_BASE, no trailing slash. Used by read_raw_edf,
#   create_study_from_upload (SAS), and generate_ai_report (pipeline trigger).
# SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY — also used by read_raw_edf + read_api_proxy to append
#   study_pipeline_events (omit only if you accept missing edge-side pipeline rows).
#
# C-Plane Container Apps env (blob read acceleration for viewer / SAS URLs):
# AFD_BLOB_HOST — optional; Azure Front Door hostname for the storage origin so read SAS
#   hits CDN/edge instead of *.blob.core.windows.net directly.
# CPLANE_MAX_CONCURRENT_JOBS — optional; default 2 ESF conversions per replica (RAM/CPU bound).
#
# C-Plane + I-Plane (Container Apps) — same Supabase project as the app (service role, not VITE_):
# SUPABASE_URL, SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY — required to append study_pipeline_events and to PATCH
#   studies to failed when C-Plane exhausts; I-Plane logs mind/run steps the same way.
